OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Mary
OL,4,CCholwill
OL,6,F"Three searchlights in different areas
OL,7,Fin Dorset would bring their lights up
OL,8,Fto a point where the pilot knew that's
OL,9,Fwhere he could land.
OL,11,F"We often had phone calls saying
OL,12,F'thank you, you have got our plane
OL,13,Fhome safely.' That was always very
OL,14,Fsatisfying."
OL,16,FIn the weeks leading up to Normandy
OL,17,Fshe was in and around Wimborne Minster.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/8
