OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Mary
OL,4,CCholwill
OL,6,F"I was on plotting and switchboards.
OL,7,FWith the plotting we had to plot the
OL,8,Fcourse of the aeroplanes and the big
OL,9,Fplotting boards were at Middle Wallop
OL,10,Fso we were taking map references for
OL,11,F(the Army) to be able to follow the
OL,12,Fcourse of the aeroplanes as they flew
OL,13,Fover.
OL,15,F"There were soldiers and lorries and
OL,16,Fall sorts of things that were stacking
OL,17,Fup but I don't think we really noticed
OL,18,Fit and then we get to the sixth (of
OL,19,FJune) everybody's gone.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/8
