OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Mary
OL,4,CCholwill
OL,6,F"We woke up one morning and all the
OL,7,Fsquaddies had gone so there was
OL,8,Fnothing for us to do. The squaddies
OL,9,Fgone and the ATS left behind. Of
OL,10,Fcourse that was D-Day.
OL,12,F"We milled around for days, all the
OL,13,FATS, the WAAFS and the Wrens (Female
OL,14,Fair force and naval personnel) -
OL,15,Fanyone who didn't have a job. We went
OL,16,Fup to a holding unit in Northampton
OL,17,Fand there we were sorted out for our
OL,18,Fnew jobs. We didn't have much to do
OL,19,Fthen because all the action was over
OL,20,Fin France."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/8
